Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro, Telecom Argentina and YPF

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-05-05T20:53:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-telecom-argentina-and-ypf.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 1.4 percent to 3,305.69.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)   retreated the most in a week,
sinking 1.9 percent to 15.90 pesos. Argentine sovereign bond
prices fell today, which signals lower values for banks’ fixed-
income holdings.  Telecom  Argentina  SA (TECO2 AF) rose 1.3 percent to 20.25
pesos. Argentina’s second-largest telephone company has gained 6
percent in the past three days, the steepest three-day gain in
six months, after reporting May 3 a 53 percent increase in
first-quarter profit from a year earlier.  YPF SA (YPFD)   fell 0.3 percent to 176.5 pesos.
Argentina’s billionaire Eskenazi family has agreed to pay $1.3
billion to boost its stake to about 25 percent in Repsol YPF
SA’s Argentine unit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
